## Architecture — Factory Pattern

This MCP server creates typed objects from LLM input. Each tool is a factory
that validates input, instantiates an object, registers it, and returns it.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Input[LLM Input] --> Validate[Validate Schema]
    Validate -->|ok| Factory[Factory.create]
    Validate -->|fail| Error[Return Error]
    Factory --> Register[Register in Registry]
    Register --> Return[Return Object]
```

## Structure

```
src/{{snakeCase name}}/
  server.py          # FastMCP server
  factories/         # one factory per object type
  validators/        # JSON Schema validators
  registry/          # registry of created objects
```

